ssets: Map<string, Buffer>;  // output path -> binary data\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;   // shared plugin data store\n}\n\n// Plugin lifecycle hooks\ninterface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n\n// Plugin interface\ninterface Plugin {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: string[];  // names of plugins this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;\n}\n\n// Template interface\ninterface Template {\n  name: string;\n  render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string;\n}\n```\n\n### 2. **engine.ts** (`/workspace/src/core/engine.ts`)\nThe core build engine - `BuildEngine` class with:\n\n**Properties:**\n- `plugins: Plugin[]` - registered plugins\n- `templates: Map<string, Template>` - registered templates\n- `config: SiteConfig` - site configuration\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `registerPlugin(plugin)` - adds a plugin\n- `registerTemplate(template)` - adds a template\n- `resolvePluginOrder()` - topological sort of plugins by dependencies (detects circular and missing dependencies)\n- `build(files)` - executes the build pipeline:\n  1. Creates BuildContext with empty output/assets/data maps\n  2. Resolves plugin execution order\n  3. Runs `beforeBuild` hooks in order\n  4. Runs `transformContent` hooks on all files in order\n  5. Renders templates with transformed files\n  6. Runs `afterBuild` hooks\n  7. Returns populated BuildContext\n- `getPlugins()` - returns copy of plugins array\n- `getTemplates()` - returns copy of templates map\n\n### 3. **templates.ts** (`/workspace/src/core/templates.ts`)\nFactory functions for built-in templates:\n\n**createDefaultTemplate()** - Standard article template with:\n- HTML5 structure\n- `<title>` with file title and site title\n- `<h1>` header with title\n- Optional `<time>` element with date\n- Content in `<div class=\"content\">`\n\n**createListTemplate()** - List-style template with:\n- HTML5 structure\n- `<h1>` header\n- Content in `<div class=\"list\">`\n\n### 4. **index.ts** (`/workspace/src/core/index.js`)\nMain export file re-exporting:\n- `BuildEngine` class\n- `createDefaultTemplate`, `createListTemplate` functions\n- All type definitions\n\n---\n\n## Test Files (tests/)\n\n### 1. **core.test.ts** (`/workspace/tests/core.test.ts`)\nComprehensive tests for BuildEngine (16 test cases):\n- Plugin registration\n- Template registration\n- Building with default/list templates\n- Raw content output when no template\n- Plugin lifecycle hooks (beforeBuild, transformContent, afterBuild)\n- Plugin dependency resolution and ordering\n- Circular dependency detection\n- Missing dependency detection\n- Multiple plugins transforming content in order\n- Shared data store functionality\n- File metadata preservation\n- Empty file list handling\n\n### 2. **search-index.test.ts** (`/workspace/tests/plugins/search-index.test.ts`)\nTests for search index plugin (8 test cases):\n- Generates `search-index.json` file\n- Index entries contain title, slug, plain text content\n- HTML tags stripped from indexed content\n- Code blocks included in searchable text\n- Handles empty file lists\n- Valid JSON output\n- Tags included in index entries\n\n### 3. **rss-feed.test.ts** (`/workspace/tests/plugins/rss-feed.test.ts`)\nTests for RSS feed plugin (7 test cases):\n- Generates valid RSS 2.0 XML\n- Feed items contain HTML content (not raw markdown)\n- Feed items include category tags from taxonomy\n- Channel title from config\n- Items sorted by date (newest first)\n- Handles files without dates\n- Feed links use baseUrl from config\n\n### 4. **sitemap.test.ts** (`/workspace/tests/plugins/sitemap.test.ts`)\nTests for sitemap plugin (8 test cases):\n- Generates `sitemap.xml` file\n- Includes all content page URLs\n- Includes taxonomy tag page URLs\n- Includes feed.xml URL\n- URLs use baseUrl from config\n- Valid XML structure\n- Handles sites with no tag pages\n\n### 5. **dev-server.test.ts** (`/workspace/tests/plugins/dev-server.test.ts`)\nTests for dev-server plugin (7 test cases):\n- Stores dev-server-config in ctx.data\n- Config includes port setting (default 3000)\n- Config includes asset routes from asset-pipeline plugin\n- Config includes search index path\n- Config includes content routes\n- Handles missing asset-pipeline data gracefully\n- DevServerConfig interface with port, routes, assetPaths, searchIndexPath\n\n### 6. **asset-pipeline.test.ts** (`/workspace/tests/plugins/asset-pipeline.test.ts`)\nTests for asset-pipeline plugin (8 test cases):\n- Rewrites relative image URLs to `/assets/` path\n- Rewrites relative link URLs to `/assets/` path\n- Leaves absolute URLs unchanged\n- Generates asset manifest in ctx.data\n- Handles files with no asset references\n- Handles multiple assets in one file\n- Asset manifest includes all discovered assets\n- Does not double-process already-rewritten URLs\n\n### 7. **taxonomy.test.ts** (`/workspace/tests/plugins/taxonomy.test.ts`)\nTests for taxonomy plugin (8 test cases):\n- Builds tag index from file tags\n- Generates tag listing pages in ctx.output\n- Handles files with no tags\n- Handles files with multiple tags\n- Tag pages list all files with that tag\n- Stores tag map in ctx.data\n- Handles empty file list\n- Tags are case-normalized to lowercase\n\n### 8. **markdown-ext.test.ts** (`/workspace/tests/plugins/markdown-ext.test.ts`)\nTests for markdown-ext plugin (8 test cases):\n- Converts basic markdown to HTML\n- Handles footnotes with `[^1]` syntax\n- Renders footnote section at bottom\n- Converts `:::note` container to admonition div\n- Converts `:::warning` container to admonition div\n- Converts `:::tip` container to admonition div\n- Preserves existing HTML in content\n- Handles empty content\n\n### 9. **syntax-highlight.test.ts** (`/workspace/tests/plugins/syntax-highlight.test.ts`)\nTests for syntax-highlight plugin (8 test cases):\n- Adds language class to code blocks\n- Adds data-language attribute to pre tags\n- Handles multiple code blocks in one file\n- Handles code blocks with no language specified\n- Adds highlighted class to processed blocks\n- Preserves code block content\n- Handles empty code blocks\n- Does not modify inline code\n\n---\n\n## Plugin Interface Details\n\nAll plugins follow the **Plugin** interface:\n\n```typescript\ninterface Plugin {\n  name: string;                    // unique plugin identifier\n  version: string;                 // plugin version\n  dependencies: string[];          // array of plugin names this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;             // lifecycle hooks\n}\n```\n\n**PluginHooks** provides three optional lifecycle hooks:\n\n1. **beforeBuild(ctx)** - Runs once before processing any files\n   - Used for setup, initialization, building indexes\n   - Can modify ctx.data, ctx.files, ctx.output, ctx.assets\n   - Runs in dependency order\n\n2. **transformContent(file, ctx)** - Runs for each file\n   - Transforms individual content files\n   - Called for each file, in dependency order across plugins\n   - Must return transformed ContentFile\n   - Can be sync or async\n   - Runs after all beforeBuild hooks\n\n3. **afterBuild(ctx)** - Runs once after all files processed\n   - Used for post-processing, final output generation\n   - Can read from ctx.files (original), ctx.output (rendered files)\n   - Runs in dependency order\n   - Runs after all transformContent hooks\n\n---\n\n## Build Pipeline Execution Order\n\n1. All plugins registered\n2. All templates registered\n3. `build(files)` called\n4. Plugins topologically sorted by dependencies (detects circular/missing)\n5. For each plugin (in order): run `beforeBuild` hook\n6. For each plugin (in order): run `transformContent` on all files\n7. Render all transformed files with templates\n8. For each plugin (in order): run `afterBuild` hook\n9. Return BuildContext with populated output/assets/data\n\nThis DAG (Directed Acyclic Graph) plugin system ensures plugins execute in correct dependency order while allowing parallel plugin development."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: af3c085a761b40ec4 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 37140\ntool_uses: 17\nduration_ms: 30851</usage>"}]}]},"uuid":"b4afd24c-90e1-4562-baa1-0b6ea98c59f0","timestamp":"2026-03-10T20:56:53.823Z","toolUseResult":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the entire codebase structure. I need to understand:\n1. All files in src/core/ - read every file\n2. All test files in tests/ - read every file\n3. Package.json, tsconfig.json, and any config files\n4. The Plugin interface from src/core/types.ts in detail\n\nRead ALL files completely. Give me the full contents and structure.","agentId":"af3c085a761b40ec4","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've now read all the files. Let me provide you with a comprehensive summary of the entire codebase structure:\n\n## Codebase Structure Overview\n\n### Project Configuration Files\n\n**package.json** (`/workspace/package.json`)\n- Name: `bench-ssg-toolkit`\n- Version: 1.0.0\n- Description: SSG Toolkit benchmark - static site generator with DAG plugin system\n- Type: ES Module\n- Main entry: `dist/core/index.js`\n- Scripts: build, lint, test\n- Dependencies: express, marked\n- Dev Dependencies: TypeScript 5.9.3, Vitest 2.1.9, ESLint with TypeScript support\n\n**tsconfig.json** (`/workspace/tsconfig.json`)\n- Target: ES2022\n- Module: Node16 with Node16 moduleResolution\n- Strict mode enabled\n- Output: `./dist`\n- Root: `./src`\n\n**vitest.config.ts** (`/workspace/vitest.config.ts`)\n- Global test mode enabled\n- Test timeout: 10000ms\n\n---\n\n## Core Library Files (src/core/)\n\n### 1. **types.ts** (`/workspace/src/core/types.ts`)\nComplete type definitions for the SSG system:\n\n```typescript\n// Site configuration\ninterface SiteConfig {\n  title: string;\n  baseUrl: stri